5:T4b8,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"SoftwareApplication","@id":"https://www.xrnotify.io/#app","name":"XRNotify","description":"Real-time webhook notification platform for the XRP Ledger.","url":"https://www.xrnotify.io","applicationCategory":"DeveloperApplication","operatingSystem":"Web","offers":[{"@type":"Offer","name":"Free","price":"0","priceCurrency":"USD","description":"1,000 events/month, 2 webhooks"},{"@type":"Offer","name":"Starter","price":"29.00","priceCurrency":"USD","description":"50,000 events/month, 10 webhooks, WebSocket access"},{"@type":"Offer","name":"Pro","price":"99.00","priceCurrency":"USD","description":"500,000 events/month, 50 webhooks, priority delivery"}],"creator":{"@id":"https://www.jonomor.com/ali-morgan#person"},"publisher":{"@id":"https://www.jonomor.com/#organization"},"isPartOf":{"@id":"https://www.jonomor.com/#organization"},"featureList":["Real-time XRPL event ingestion","HMAC-SHA256 signed webhook delivery","Automatic retries with exponential backoff","Dead-letter queue for failed deliveries","Event replay and reprocessing","23+ XRPL event types supported","Developer dashboard with delivery logs","Per-webhook filtering by event type and account"]}6:Tcff,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","@id":"https://www.xrnotify.io/#faqpage","name":"XRNotify FAQ — Common Questions About XRPL Webhooks","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What is XRNotify?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"XRNotify is a real-time webhook notification platform for the XRP Ledger. It monitors XRPL transactions as they confirm on-chain, normalizes them into clean JSON schemas, and delivers them to your endpoints via HMAC-signed HTTPS POST requests. XRNotify eliminates the need to run your own XRPL node or build polling infrastructure."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What XRPL events does XRNotify support?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"XRNotify supports 23+ event types across all major XRPL transaction categories: payments (XRP and issued tokens), NFT operations (minting, burning, offers, transfers), DEX trades (OfferCreate, OfferCancel, AMM operations), trustline changes (TrustSet), escrow events (create, finish, cancel), check operations, and account-level changes like settings modifications and deletions."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How does webhook delivery work?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"When an XRPL transaction matches your configured filters, XRNotify normalizes the event, signs the payload with your webhook secret using HMAC-SHA256, and delivers it as an HTTPS POST to your endpoint. If delivery fails, XRNotify retries with exponential backoff (up to 10 attempts over 12 hours). Events that exhaust all retries are moved to a dead-letter queue for manual inspection and replay."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is XRNotify free?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"XRNotify offers a free tier with 1,000 events per month and 2 webhook endpoints — enough for testing and hobby projects. Paid plans start at $29/month (Starter: 50,000 events, 10 webhooks, WebSocket streaming) and $99/month (Pro: 500,000 events, 50 webhooks, priority delivery). Enterprise plans with custom SLAs are available on request."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How do I verify webhook signatures?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Every XRNotify webhook includes an X-XRNotify-Signature header containing an HMAC-SHA256 hash of the request body, computed using your webhook signing secret. To verify, compute the HMAC-SHA256 of the raw request body with your secret and compare it to the header value using a constant-time comparison function to prevent timing attacks."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Who built XRNotify?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"XRNotify was built by Ali Morgan, founder of Jonomor, a systems architecture studio focused on AI Visibility and real-time infrastructure intelligence. XRNotify is the XRPL instrumentation layer of the Jonomor ecosystem, which also includes Guard-Clause, MyPropOps, The Neutral Bridge, Evenfield, and H.U.N.I.E."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is XRNotify part of a larger ecosystem?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. XRNotify is part of the Jonomor ecosystem, a suite of interconnected software products built by Ali Morgan. Within the ecosystem, XRNotify serves as the real-time observation layer — detecting XRPL events at the point of origin before they flow through interpretation and operational layers in other Jonomor properties."}}]}0:["pQjrRFT3j-NbWRfetFzsE",[[["",{"children":["docs",{"children":["guides",{"children":["handling-failures",{"children":["__PAGE__",{}]}]}]}]},"$undefined","$undefined",true],["",{"children":["docs",{"children":["guides",{"children":["handling-failures",{"children":["__PAGE__",{},[["$L1",["$","div",null,{"className":"min-h-screen bg-[#0a0a0f] text-white antialiased","children":[["$","nav",null,{"className":"border-b border-zinc-800/50","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-4 flex items-center justify-between","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"flex items-center gap-2 text-sm","children":[["$","$L2",null,{"href":"/docs","className":"text-zinc-500 hover:text-zinc-300 no-underline","children":"Docs"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-zinc-600","children":"/"}],["$","$L2",null,{"href":"/docs#guides","className":"text-zinc-500 hover:text-zinc-300 no-underline","children":"Guides"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-zinc-600","children":"/"}],["$","span",null,{"className":"text-zinc-300","children":"Handling Failures"}]]}],["$","$L2",null,{"href":"/dashboard","className":"text-zinc-400 hover:text-white transition-colors text-sm no-underline","children":"Dashboard →"}]]}]}],["$","main",null,{"className":"max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-12","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"inline-block text-xs font-medium text-emerald-400 bg-emerald-500/10 border border-emerald-500/20 rounded px-2 py-0.5 mb-4","children":"Guides"}],["$","h1",null,{"className":"text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-3","children":"Handling Webhook Failures"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-zinc-400 text-lg leading-relaxed","children":"Understand how XRNotify retries failed deliveries, how to recover from extended outages with the Replay API, and how to build an idempotent handler that safely processes retried events."}]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4","children":"Retry policy overview"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-zinc-300 text-sm mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"XRNotify automatically retries a delivery whenever your endpoint returns a non-2xx HTTP status or does not respond within the 10-second timeout. Retries follow an exponential backoff schedule with ±10% jitter:"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"overflow-x-auto mb-4","children":["$","table",null,{"className":"w-full text-sm border-collapse","children":[["$","thead",null,{"children":["$","tr",null,{"className":"border-b border-zinc-800","children":[["$","th",null,{"className":"text-left py-2 pr-6 text-zinc-400 font-medium","children":"Attempt"}],["$","th",null,{"className":"text-left py-2 pr-6 text-zinc-400 font-medium","children":"Delay"}],["$","th",null,{"className":"text-left py-2 text-zinc-400 font-medium","children":"Total elapsed"}]]}]}],["$","tbody",null,{"className":"divide-y divide-zinc-800/50","children":[["$","tr","1 (initial)",{"children":[["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2 pr-6 text-zinc-300","children":"1 (initial)"}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2 pr-6 text-zinc-300","children":"Immediate"}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2 text-zinc-300","children":"0s"}]]}],["$","tr","2",{"children":[["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2 pr-6 text-zinc-300","children":"2"}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2 pr-6 text-zinc-300","children":"1 minute"}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2 text-zinc-300","children":"~1m"}]]}],["$","tr","3",{"children":[["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2 pr-6 text-zinc-300","children":"3"}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2 pr-6 text-zinc-300","children":"5 minutes"}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2 text-zinc-300","children":"~6m"}]]}],["$","tr","4",{"children":[["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2 pr-6 text-zinc-300","children":"4"}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2 pr-6 text-zinc-300","children":"30 minutes"}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2 text-zinc-300","children":"~36m"}]]}],["$","tr","5",{"children":[["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2 pr-6 text-zinc-300","children":"5"}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2 pr-6 text-zinc-300","children":"2 hours"}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2 text-zinc-300","children":"~2.6h"}]]}],["$","tr","6",{"children":[["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2 pr-6 text-zinc-300","children":"6"}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2 pr-6 text-zinc-300","children":"6 hours"}],["$","td",null,{"className":"py-2 text-zinc-300","children":"~8.6h"}]]}]]}]]}]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-zinc-400 text-sm leading-relaxed","children":["After 6 attempts the delivery status becomes"," ",["$","code",null,{"className":"text-emerald-400 bg-zinc-800 px-1 rounded","children":"failed"}],". No further automatic retries occur, but you can trigger a manual retry at any time. See the full schedule in the"," ",["$","$L2",null,{"href":"/docs/reference/retry-policy","className":"text-emerald-400 hover:text-emerald-300","children":"Retry Policy reference"}],"."]}]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4","children":"Checking failed deliveries"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-zinc-300 text-sm mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"Query the deliveries API with a status filter to see everything that failed for a given webhook:"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-4 overflow-x-auto mb-4","children":["$","pre",null,{"className":"text-zinc-300 text-sm font-mono whitespace-pre","children":"curl \"https://api.xrnotify.io/v1/deliveries?status=failed&webhook_id=wh_abc\" \\\n  -H \"X-XRNotify-Key: xrn_live_xxx\""}]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-zinc-300 text-sm leading-relaxed","children":["Each delivery object in the response includes"," ",["$","code",null,{"className":"text-emerald-400 bg-zinc-800 px-1 rounded","children":"last_error"}],","," ",["$","code",null,{"className":"text-emerald-400 bg-zinc-800 px-1 rounded","children":"attempts"}],", and"," ",["$","code",null,{"className":"text-emerald-400 bg-zinc-800 px-1 rounded","children":"next_retry_at"}]," so you can understand exactly what went wrong. You can also view this on the"," ",["$","$L2",null,{"href":"/dashboard/deliveries","className":"text-emerald-400 hover:text-emerald-300","children":"Deliveries page"}]," ","in the dashboard."]}]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4","children":"Manual retry (single delivery)"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-zinc-300 text-sm mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"If a delivery has exhausted its automatic retries, or you want to force an immediate re-attempt before the next scheduled retry, call the retry endpoint:"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-4 overflow-x-auto mb-4","children":["$","pre",null,{"className":"text-zinc-300 text-sm font-mono whitespace-pre","children":"curl -X POST https://api.xrnotify.io/v1/deliveries/dlv_abc123/retry \\\n  -H \"X-XRNotify-Key: xrn_live_xxx\""}]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-zinc-400 text-sm","children":["The delivery will be dispatched immediately. The response includes the new"," ",["$","code",null,{"className":"text-emerald-400 bg-zinc-800 px-1 rounded","children":"status"}]," and"," ",["$","code",null,{"className":"text-emerald-400 bg-zinc-800 px-1 rounded","children":"response_code"}]," once the attempt completes."]}]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4","children":"Bulk recovery with the Replay API"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-zinc-300 text-sm mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"If your endpoint was down for several hours and many deliveries failed, retrying them individually is impractical. The Replay API re-delivers all events matching a time window and optional event type filter in a single call:"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-4 overflow-x-auto mb-4","children":["$","pre",null,{"className":"text-zinc-300 text-sm font-mono whitespace-pre","children":"curl -X POST https://api.xrnotify.io/v1/replay \\\n  -H \"X-XRNotify-Key: xrn_live_xxx\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\n    \"webhook_id\": \"wh_abc123\",\n    \"filters\": {\n      \"since\": \"2024-01-15T00:00:00Z\",\n      \"until\": \"2024-01-15T06:00:00Z\",\n      \"event_types\": [\"payment.xrp\"]\n    }\n  }'"}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"bg-emerald-500/10 border border-emerald-500/20 rounded-lg p-3 text-sm text-zinc-300","children":["Because the Replay API re-delivers events, your handler will receive"," ",["$","code",null,{"className":"text-emerald-400","children":"X-XRNotify-Delivery-Id"}]," values that differ from the original delivery IDs. Ensure your idempotency key is derived from the ",["$","strong",null,{"className":"text-white","children":"event_id"}]," field in the body (which is deterministic) rather than the delivery ID header."]}]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4","children":"Idempotency"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-zinc-300 text-sm mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":["Because XRNotify retries deliveries, your endpoint may receive the same event more than once. Use the"," ",["$","code",null,{"className":"text-emerald-400 bg-zinc-800 px-1 rounded","children":"X-XRNotify-Delivery-Id"}]," header to record processed deliveries and skip duplicates:"]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-4 overflow-x-auto mb-4","children":["$","pre",null,{"className":"text-zinc-300 text-sm font-mono whitespace-pre","children":"app.post('/webhooks', express.raw({ type: 'application/json' }), async (req, res) => {\n  // 1. Verify signature first\n  if (!verifySignature(req.body, req.headers['x-xrnotify-signature'], process.env.WEBHOOK_SECRET)) {\n    return res.status(401).end();\n  }\n\n  const deliveryId = req.headers['x-xrnotify-delivery-id'];\n\n  // 2. Check if already processed\n  const processed = await cache.get(`delivery:${deliveryId}`);\n  if (processed) return res.sendStatus(200); // Already done — safe to ack\n\n  // 3. Process event\n  const event = JSON.parse(req.body);\n  await processEvent(event);\n\n  // 4. Mark as processed with a 24-hour TTL\n  await cache.set(`delivery:${deliveryId}`, 'done', 86400);\n\n  res.sendStatus(200);\n});"}]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-zinc-400 text-sm leading-relaxed","children":"Any in-memory store, Redis, or database table works for the idempotency cache. The 24-hour TTL is sufficient because XRNotify's retry window is under 9 hours."}]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4","children":"Making your endpoint resilient"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-zinc-300 text-sm mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"A well-designed webhook endpoint minimises the chance of generating failures in the first place:"}],["$","ul",null,{"className":"space-y-3 text-zinc-300 text-sm","children":[["$","li",null,{"className":"flex gap-3","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"text-emerald-400 shrink-0 mt-0.5","children":"→"}],["$","span",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"className":"text-white","children":"Respond within 10 seconds."}]," XRNotify's delivery timeout is 10 seconds. If your processing takes longer, push the event to an internal queue (SQS, BullMQ, etc.) immediately and acknowledge with ",["$","code",null,{"className":"text-emerald-400 bg-zinc-800 px-1 rounded","children":"200 OK"}],". Process asynchronously."]}]]}],["$","li",null,{"className":"flex gap-3","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"text-emerald-400 shrink-0 mt-0.5","children":"→"}],["$","span",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"className":"text-white","children":"Always return 200 on receipt."}]," Acknowledge the delivery as soon as you've safely queued the event — even if downstream processing fails. Track your own processing failures in a dead-letter queue separate from XRNotify's retry mechanism."]}]]}],["$","li",null,{"className":"flex gap-3","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"text-emerald-400 shrink-0 mt-0.5","children":"→"}],["$","span",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"className":"text-white","children":"Monitor your own queue."}]," XRNotify's retry mechanism ensures delivery to your endpoint, but it cannot guarantee that your internal processing succeeds. Set up alerts on your dead-letter queue depth."]}]]}],["$","li",null,{"className":"flex gap-3","children":[["$","span",null,{"className":"text-emerald-400 shrink-0 mt-0.5","children":"→"}],["$","span",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"className":"text-white","children":"Use a valid TLS certificate."}]," Expired or self-signed certificates cause immediate failures. Use a certificate from a public CA and set up automatic renewal (e.g., Let's Encrypt with Certbot)."]}]]}]]}]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"bg-amber-500/10 border border-amber-500/20 rounded-lg p-3 text-sm text-zinc-300","children":[["$","strong",null,{"className":"text-amber-300","children":"Warning:"}]," If your endpoint returns 5xx errors consistently, XRNotify may automatically disable the webhook after 100 consecutive failures. You will receive an email notification when this happens. Re-enable the webhook from the dashboard or via"," ",["$","code",null,{"className":"text-emerald-400","children":"PATCH /v1/webhooks/{id}"}]," ","once your endpoint is healthy."]}]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4","children":"Delivery health dashboard"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-zinc-300 text-sm mb-4 leading-relaxed","children":"The Stats endpoint returns aggregate delivery metrics for a webhook over the last 24 hours:"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-4 overflow-x-auto mb-4","children":["$","pre",null,{"className":"text-zinc-300 text-sm font-mono whitespace-pre","children":"curl \"https://api.xrnotify.io/v1/webhooks/wh_abc123/stats\" \\\n  -H \"X-XRNotify-Key: xrn_live_xxx\""}]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-zinc-300 text-sm leading-relaxed","children":["You can also view a real-time success rate chart and per-delivery logs on the"," ",["$","$L2",null,{"href":"/dashboard/deliveries","className":"text-emerald-400 hover:text-emerald-300","children":"Deliveries page"}]," ","in the dashboard — no API call needed."]}]]}],["$","section",null,{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-xl font-semibold text-white mb-4","children":"Next steps"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3","children":[["$","$L2","/docs/reference/retry-policy",{"href":"/docs/reference/retry-policy","className":"block bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-4 hover:border-zinc-700 transition-colors no-underline","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"text-sm font-medium text-white mb-1","children":"Retry Policy Reference"}],["$","div",null,{"className":"text-xs text-zinc-500","children":"Full retry schedule, jitter formula, and auto-disable logic"}]]}],["$","$L2","/docs/api/replay",{"href":"/docs/api/replay","className":"block bg-zinc-900 border border-z